  • Method Details

    • extractRelationship

      public RelationVO extractRelationship(org.neo4j.driver.Value relation)
      Extracts and converts a relationship value into a RelationVO object. This method checks if the provided relationship value is null. If it is null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. If the value is a valid relationship, it is converted into a RelationVO object by calling the `setRelationVOInfo` method.
      Parameters:
      relation - The relationship value to be extracted.
      Returns:
      A RelationVO object representing the extracted relationship.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the provided relationship value is null.

    • extractRelationships

      public List<RelationVO> extractRelationships(org.neo4j.driver.Value relationshipsValue)
      Extracts relationships from a given relationships value. If the input relationships value is null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown with a specific error message. If the input relationships value is valid, it extracts and returns a list of RelationVO objects.
      Parameters:
      relationshipsValue - the relationships value to extract relationships from
      Returns:
      a list of RelationVO objects representing the relationships
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the input relationships value is null
